  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (44f3a4b 2022-07-17T00:13:18.493764624Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge script , forge test\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nI have the following .env:\r\n\r\n`UINT_VALUE=115792089237316195423570985008687907853269984665640564039457584007913129639935`\r\n\r\nAnd this Makefile:\r\n\r\n```\r\n-include .env\r\n\r\ninstall :; forge install foundry-rs/forge-std && forge install dapphub/ds-test\r\n\r\ntest :; forge test\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd a test file:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunction testEnvironment() public {\r\n\t\tstring memory key = \"UINT_VALUE\";\r\n\t\tuint256 expected = type(uint256).max;\r\n\t\t// vm.setEnv(key, \"115792089237316195423570985008687907853269984665640564039457584007913129639935\");\r\n\t\tuint256 output = hevm.envUint(key);\r\n\t\tassert(output == expected);\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\nRunning `make test` does not work unless I change my Makefile to:\r\n\r\n```\r\n-include .env\r\n\r\ninstall :; forge install foundry-rs/forge-std && forge install dapphub/ds-test\r\n\r\ntest :; UINT_VALUE=${UINT_VALUE} forge test\r\n```\r\n\r\nSourcing .env in my CLI and running `forge test` does not work either. The only thing that works is inlining the env var prior to running `forge`. \r\n\r\n```\r\nsource .env\r\necho $UINT_VALUE  => 115792089237316195423570985008687907853269984665640564039457584007913129639935\r\nforge test => ERROR\r\nUINT_VALUE=${UINT_VALUE} forge test => WORKS!\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nThe error I 'm getting:\r\n\r\n```\r\nFailed tests:\r\n[FAIL. Reason: environment variable not found] testEnvironment() (gas: 3444)\r\n```",
