    "body": "This is not an error in Foundry, the Makefile is just wrong I think. I've always had to do something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\n-include .env\r\nexport\r\n```\r\n\r\nOtherwise the variables would be local to the Makefile, not global (and thus not affect the child processes)\r\n\r\nEdit: Same for when you source your `.env` - it is just setting the variables locally to your shell, not exporting them. In bash, you have to do: `export $(cat .env | xargs)`, or alternatively prefix each line in your `.env` file with `export`",
